Reasoning: The paper deals with decision trees for binary classification, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses impurity functions, which are used to measure the quality of splits in decision trees, and this falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions class weighting, which is a technique used to handle imbalanced datasets, and this falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well as cs.ST (Statistics).
